CRUD is a acronym for Create, Read, Update, Delete.
CRUD is neccesary for implementation of a persistant storage application
persistent storage device means any device that retains power when the device is powered off(hard disc)


     CREATE
The create function allows users to create a new record(row) in the database.
It does not allow to create a new attribute(column).


     READ
It is used to find specific records in database


     UPDATE
It is used to modify existing records.


     DELETE
It is used to remove records from the database
